# Improve Riddle Segmentation & Display (Duration Filtering)

The goal is to prevent the bot from downloading massive compilation videos (e.g., 6GB+) by filtering out any video longer than **20 minutes**.

## Proposed Changes

### [MODIFY] [youtube_client.py](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/clipper/src/clipper/youtube_client.py)
- **Metadata Fetch**: After getting the list of video IDs from `search().list`, make a batch call to [videos().list(id=..., part='contentDetails')](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/clipper/src/clipper/youtube_client.py#48-85).
- **Parsing**: Parse the ISO 8601 duration (e.g., `PT1H5M`) into seconds.
- **Filtering**: Drop any video > 1200 seconds.

### [MODIFY] [riddle_bot.py](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/clipper/riddle_bot.py)
- **Update Usage**: Pass `max_duration_seconds=1200` to [get_channel_videos](file:///c:/Users/rovie%20segubre/clipper/src/clipper/youtube_client.py#48-85) (or handle it inside the client).

